100 Crowns/Chocolate City signee and rapper, Blaqbonez has revealed his headline concert will hold on Valentine’s eve. The controversial rapper registered himself as an anti-love personality with the release of his album, “Sex over Love” on April 30, 2021. As he continues to preach against love, ‘Emeka the Stallion’ in a recent Instagram post shared a flyer announcing his musical crusade tagged “Breaking the Yoke of Love” slated to hold on February 13, 2022. He wrote: “MY HEADLINE CONCERT, ‘BREAKING THE YOKE OF LOVE’, FEBRUARY 13TH. ABOUT TO BE THE CRAZIEST SHOW EVER.”   ‘What Allah has joined together, no herdsman can separate’     Obi Cubana to Phyno: you look like Jesus     Sammie Okposo told me to get rid of pregnancy- African Doll   - Advertisement - On August 18, 2021, Blaqbonez had revealed the title of his next album will be titled “Young Preacher.” Speaking on this, ‘Mr Boombastic’ tweeted: “My next album is called ‘young preacher’, been working on it since the day I dropped “sex over love.” On January 8, 2022, he shared a new video snippet for one of the songs from his anticipated album, “Young Preacher” scheduled for release this year.